result.execSummary:
The defendant Joseph R Schultz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 11:07am [mo]
Defendant Joseph R Schultz in court with Attorney Karl Huebner.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.

On the Defendant's 5/20/2015 Motion to Modify Bond: 
--The State opposes the Defendant's Motion; gives reasoning
--Arguments given by Attorney Huebner in support of Motion

The Court inquires of Defense the Returned Mail in file. Mr. Schultz confirms that the address on file in correct. 
The Court questions Ms. Morgan about letter she wrote to the Court and about domestic violence in relationships.

The Court grants the Motion to Modify Bond.
The Court modifies Mr. Schultz bond to remove the condition that prohibits contact with Crystal Morgan. 
The Court adds the condition the Mr. Schultz and Crystal Morgan may not discuss the facts of the case, except in a counseling session with a counselor 

The Court dicusses with Ms. Morgan the importance of not discussing the case and what to do if Mr. Schultz should threaten her and her children.
